00:54:12.572 --> 00:54:15.402
I'm actually going home in Namhae.

792
00:54:15.402 --> 00:54:16.672
What about your job?

793
00:54:17.712 --> 00:54:18.942
I quit it.

794
00:54:22.411 --> 00:54:25.982
I want to thank you for renting me such a nice room.

795
00:54:28.081 --> 00:54:31.692
I could write my first proper scenario here thanks to you,

796
00:54:32.491 --> 00:54:34.661
even though it didn't go well.

797
00:54:35.721 --> 00:54:38.331
You'll do well wherever you go.

798
00:54:38.592 --> 00:54:40.391
You're a very responsible person.

799
00:54:41.561 --> 00:54:45.572
You scored the highest among all the tenants who lived here.

800
00:54:46.371 --> 00:54:50.042
That's right. You'll do well too.

801
00:54:50.272 --> 00:54:53.511
You'll marry a nice woman soon as well.

802
00:54:54.681 --> 00:54:55.842
I don't know.

803
00:54:56.141 --> 00:54:58.982
I don't know if I will be able to marry someone.

804
00:54:59.781 --> 00:55:02.781
Why not? You proposed to me as well.

805
00:55:03.322 --> 00:55:04.721
Why wouldn't you be able to get married?

806
00:55:05.451 --> 00:55:06.692
It's because it was you.

807
00:55:09.721 --> 00:55:11.431
I did that because it was you.

808
00:55:12.561 --> 00:55:14.732
You scored the highest as the tenant.

809
00:55:15.931 --> 00:55:18.831
I need you, not a marriage.

810
00:55:19.031 --> 00:55:20.402
That's why I proposed to you.

811
00:55:22.002 --> 00:55:26.072
I knew it was not the right moment to fall for him.

812
00:55:27.942 --> 00:55:29.581
I need a roommate...

813
00:55:30.112 --> 00:55:33.351
who can guarantee me monthly rent instead of marriage.

814
00:55:36.281 --> 00:55:37.422
But still,

815
00:55:39.851 --> 00:55:41.121
it was the first time...

816
00:55:47.362 --> 00:55:50.331
hearing that someone needs me.

817
00:55:54.502 --> 00:55:56.871
(Boarding Direction)

818
00:56:00.712 --> 00:56:02.641
- Where are you heading? - The earliest ticket to Namhae.

819
00:56:03.141 --> 00:56:04.581
Throughout my life in 20s,

820
00:56:06.081 --> 00:56:09.552
I worked hard to be a person who's needed for something.

821
00:56:19.891 --> 00:56:22.502
I crossed the Han River Bridge whenever I went through a hard time.

822
00:56:23.561 --> 00:56:25.302
Looking over Han River,

823
00:56:27.101 --> 00:56:28.842
I thought there might be...

824
00:56:30.042 --> 00:56:31.741
at least one place...

825
00:56:32.612 --> 00:56:34.781
that needed me in this big city.

826
00:56:44.552 --> 00:56:46.092
That's how I thought.

827
00:57:03.101 --> 00:57:05.042
For 10 years,

828
00:57:06.471 --> 00:57:09.112
this luggage got scratched up so much like me.

829
00:57:11.011 --> 00:57:14.052
It was shiny when I first came to Seoul with it.

830
00:57:20.451 --> 00:57:23.391
(Seoul to Namhae)

831
00:57:28.061 --> 00:57:30.701
For what did I try so hard to live,

832
00:57:32.072 --> 00:57:36.201
when I'd go back to Namhae without any achievement?

833
00:57:38.471 --> 00:57:40.442
There wasn't any place for me...

834
00:57:42.612 --> 00:57:44.252
from the beginning anyway.

835
00:58:07.201 --> 00:58:08.241
What are you doing here?

836
00:58:09.741 --> 00:58:12.042
- How... - Why didn't you answer your phone?

837
00:58:14.042 --> 00:58:16.842
It ran out of battery.

838
00:58:18.581 --> 00:58:20.712
You left these in your room.

839
00:58:23.281 --> 00:58:25.491
Did you come here to give me these?

840
00:58:25.692 --> 00:58:27.692
I was on my way out,

841
00:58:28.422 --> 00:58:30.721
and I remembered you said your bus departs at 7pm.

842
00:58:32.491 --> 00:58:34.331
It seemed like you needed these.

843
00:58:38.902 --> 00:58:39.931
Yes.

844
00:58:42.042 --> 00:58:43.471
I need them.

845
00:58:43.542 --> 00:58:45.141
We'll depart shortly.

846
00:58:46.311 --> 00:58:47.411
Then, goodbye.

847
00:58:48.411 --> 00:58:49.482
Bye.

848
00:59:18.042 --> 00:59:19.342
It's because it was you.

849
00:59:20.942 --> 00:59:22.681
I did that because it was you.

850
00:59:26.712 --> 00:59:30.252
He's the first person...

851
00:59:31.951 --> 00:59:33.891
who said he needed me.

852
00:59:43.161 --> 00:59:45.802
The driver won't wait long because he's upset.

853
00:59:46.132 --> 00:59:47.471
So give me a quick answer.

854
00:59:48.471 --> 00:59:49.572
Okay.

855
00:59:50.101 --> 00:59:51.141
Will you...

856
00:59:52.141 --> 00:59:53.411
marry me?

857
00:59:56.141 --> 00:59:58.982
Hurry. He's waiting.

858
01:00:00.951 --> 01:00:01.951
Okay.

859
01:00:02.382 --> 01:00:04.451
Then I'll go unload my luggage.

860
01:00:04.951 --> 01:00:06.752
He's very upset.

861
01:00:08.092 --> 01:00:09.192
Look.

862
01:00:11.192 --> 01:00:12.831
I have something to ask before then.

863
01:00:13.061 --> 01:00:14.531
Go ahead.

864
01:00:14.931 --> 01:00:16.201
By any chance,

865
01:00:20.101 --> 01:00:21.442
do you like me?

866
01:00:24.971 --> 01:00:26.112
No.

867
01:00:35.781 --> 01:00:37.692
That's how...

868
01:00:41.592 --> 01:00:42.962
our proposal began.

869
01:01:03.311 --> 01:01:07.081
(Because This Is My First Life)

870
01:01:07.351 --> 01:01:09.681
I decided to marry my tenant today.

871
01:01:10.382 --> 01:01:12.552
Are you serious? Are you sure you're marrying a girl?

872
01:01:12.552 --> 01:01:14.792
We've known only for a short time,

873
01:01:14.792 --> 01:01:17.261
but he's someone I need.

874
01:01:17.261 --> 01:01:19.991
- You need him? - I know why you're marrying him.

875
01:01:20.232 --> 01:01:23.101
You can fool everyone, but not me.

876
01:01:23.261 --> 01:01:24.701
- She's pretty. - Is she?

877
01:01:24.831 --> 01:01:27.701
My family is very patriarchal.

878
01:01:27.772 --> 01:01:29.971
Shall I make a scene here?

879
01:01:31.141 --> 01:01:32.411
- Ta-da. - Ta-da.

880
01:01:32.542 --> 01:01:35.382
I thought he loved you at least.

881
01:01:36.241 --> 01:01:37.752
Will you be all right?

882
01:01:38.152 --> 01:01:40.011
Why do you ask such a question?

883
01:01:40.311 --> 01:01:42.221
I love him.

884
01:01:43.581 --> 01:01:46.991
Marrying this tenant is the answer indeed.

